Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with device-to-device communication in a wireless network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses resource allocation and power control problems in a wireless network, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper models the power control problem as a multiagent learning game, which falls under the scope of game theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a graph-theoretical approach for channel allocation, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper models the power control problem as a multiagent learning game, which falls under the scope of multiagent systems.
